# MCP README Sync

Whenever you modify any file under `packages/core/mcp/` (tools, handler, UI components, lib), you **must** also update `packages/core/mcp/README.md` to reflect the change before finishing.

## What to update

| Change made | README section to update |
|-------------|--------------------------|
| New or renamed file | Architecture tree (top of README) |
| New MCP tool or changed tool parameters/behaviour | MCP Tools section |
| Widget component added/modified | ChatGPT Widget UI → Components |
| Widget communication pattern changed | ChatGPT Widget UI → Widget Communication |
| Widget step/state machine changed | ChatGPT Widget UI → Widget Auth Flow |
| New server endpoint | API Integration → Endpoints |
| Auth or OAuth flow changed | Authentication Flow + Usage Example |

## Rules

- Update the README **in the same response** as the code change — never defer it.
- Keep the Architecture file tree accurate: add new files, remove deleted ones.
- The Usage Example at the bottom should always reflect the current end-to-end flow.
